# Tailwind CSS v4.0 — Agent Reference

Use this when suggesting Tailwind classes, config, or setup. Tailwind v4 differs significantly from v3.

## Installation & Setup

**v4 uses a single CSS import — no `@tailwind` directives:**

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
```

**PostCSS:** `npm i tailwindcss @tailwindcss/postcss` then add `"@tailwindcss/postcss"` to plugins.

**Vite:** Use `@tailwindcss/vite` instead of PostCSS for best performance.

## Configuration — CSS-First

**No `tailwind.config.js`.** Configure in CSS via `@theme`:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --font-display: "Satoshi", "sans-serif";
  --breakpoint-3xl: 1920px;
  --color-avocado-500: oklch(0.84 0.18 117.33);
  --ease-fluid: cubic-bezier(0.3, 0, 0, 1);
}
```

Design tokens become native CSS variables (e.g. `var(--color-avocado-500)`).

## Content Detection

**No `content` array.** v4 auto-detects source files. Use `@source` only if you need to include excluded paths:

```css
@source "../node_modules/@my-company/ui-lib";
```

## Key Utility Changes

| v3 | v4 |
|----|-----|
| `bg-gradient-to-r` | `bg-linear-to-r` |
| `bg-gradient-to-r from-X to-Y` | `bg-linear-to-r from-X to-Y` (same) |
| `grid-cols-[13]` (arbitrary) | `grid-cols-13` (built-in) |
| `data-[current]:opacity-100` (needs config) | `data-current:opacity-100` (built-in) |
| `@tailwindcss/container-queries` plugin | `@container`, `@min-*`, `@max-*` in core |

## Container Queries (Built-in)

```html
<div class="@container">
  <div class="grid-cols-1 @sm:grid-cols-3 @lg:grid-cols-4">...</div>
</div>
```

Max-width: `@max-md:grid-cols-1`. Ranges: `@min-md:@max-xl:hidden`.

## New Variants & Utilities

- **`not-*`:** `not-hover:opacity-75`, `not-supports-hanging-punctuation:px-4`
- **`starting`:** For `@starting-style` enter/exit transitions
- **3D transforms:** `rotate-x-*`, `rotate-y-*`, `scale-z-*`, `translate-z-*`, `perspective-distant`
- **Gradients:** `bg-linear-45`, `bg-conic-*`, `bg-radial-*`; modifiers like `bg-linear-to-r/oklch`

## What to Avoid

- Do not suggest `tailwind.config.js` for new v4 projects
- Do not suggest `content: [...]` — it's automatic
- Do not suggest `@tailwind base; @tailwind components; @tailwind utilities;` — use `@import "tailwindcss"`
- Do not suggest the `@tailwindcss/container-queries` plugin — container queries are built-in

## Upgrade Path

Existing v3 projects: use the [official upgrade guide](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/upgrade-guide) and automated upgrade tool.
